<taxonomicName id="B59BF6D03902FF88619966FFF44CFC77" box="[483,607,924,949]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pinnotheridae" genus="Scleroplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="40EF51413902FF88619966FFF44CFC77" box="[483,607,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Scleroplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by their relatively flat carapace that is noticeably wider than long, with WL 
<number id="C4539F743902FF8861CC66A7F7D1FC1C" box="[438,450,964,990]" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" value="3.0">3</number>
